Initial setup and communication
  1.1. Conduct initial team meeting to discuss project objectives, team roles, and responsibilities.
  1.2. Set up a communication and collaboration platform (e.g., Slack, Microsoft Teams).
  1.3. Establish a project management tool (e.g., Trello, Asana) for task tracking and progress monitoring.

Collaboration with other teams
  2.1. Meet with Team 1 to understand key event log characteristics and implemented compression techniques.
  2.2. Obtain access to the test environment and performance evaluation metrics from Team 2.
  2.3. Provide input for documentation and tutorials to Team 4.

Test plan development
  3.1. Define test objectives and scope for individual compression techniques and combinations.
  3.2. Create a detailed test schedule and assign responsibilities.
  3.3. Develop test scenarios and test cases for each compression technique and combination.

Test execution and optimization
  4.1. Execute test plan and record results for each test case.
  4.2. Analyze test results to identify optimal compression technique combinations.
  4.3. Collaborate with Team 1 to refine and optimize compression techniques based on test findings.

Keylog compression library development
  5.1. Design the architecture of the keylog compression library for QMK integration.
  5.2. Implement the optimized compression techniques within the library.
  5.3. Ensure proper modularity and compatibility with the QMK framework.

User interface design
  6.1. Define user requirements and expectations for the interface.
  6.2. Design a user-friendly interface for selecting and applying compression methods.
  6.3. Implement the interface within the keylog compression library.

Integration and testing with QMK keyboards
  7.1. Test the keylog compression library with QMK keyboards for compatibility and seamless operation.
  7.2. Identify and address any bugs or issues found during integration testing.
  7.3. Refine the library and interface as needed based on testing feedback.

Continuous improvement and optimization
  8.1. Establish a process for ongoing improvement of compression techniques based on user feedback and new developments.
  8.2. Monitor and analyze user feedback to identify areas for further optimization.
  8.3. Implement improvements and refinements to the library and compression techniques as needed.

Progress monitoring and reporting
  9.1. Update the project management tool regularly with task completion status and progress.
  9.2. Conduct regular team meetings to discuss progress, challenges, and alignment with project objectives and timelines.
  9.3. Prepare and submit progress reports to the CEO and other stakeholders as required.

Knowledge transfer and support
  10.1. Ensure proper knowledge transfer between Teams 1, 2, and 4 for effective collaboration and integration.
  10.2. Address any questions or concerns from other teams regarding the keylog compression library or compression techniques.
  10.3. Provide ongoing support to other teams as needed to ensure project success.
